yellow armpit staines how do i get rid of these stubborn stains with household items deodorant and perspiration stain removal yellow underarm shirt stains are likely caused by a combination of deodorant and perspiration many deodorants and antiperspirants contain aluminum salts when these salts are combined with laundry detergent especially in cooler water settings they are not easily dissolved and they remain on the fabric to remove the stains try soaking the shirts in warm water with an enzyme pre soak product or rubbing the soiled area with white vinegar wash in the hottest water safe for the fabric if the stain remains dampen and sprinkle stain with meat tenderizer let stand for about an hour and launder again to avoid new stains from forming always wash the shirts in the hottest water safe for the fabric also allow antiperspirant to dry completely before dressing Deodorant Laundry detergent Dry cleaning Laundry Plastic Dishwasher Textile manufacturing Washing machine Bong Sodium percarbonate Soap Tofu Aluminium Psoriasis Staining (biology) Upholstery Body odor Menstrual cup Enzyme Hyperhidrosis Water purification Sulfuric acid Kosher foods Urticaria Soy milk Sweating Coffee Acetic acid Hydrogen peroxide Dishwashing Cheese Sodium hydroxide Diaper Cantonese cuisine Jewish cuisine Sulfur Manicure Leather Black pepper Drowning Sodium hypochlorite Alum Dairy Bedbug Hypothermia Jute Cuisine of the Philippines Nuclear fallout Japanese toilet Sterilization (microbiology) Sewage treatment Thermal power station Gram staining Water Rice Air conditioning Gilding Agar plate Ammonia Cookware and bakeware 1,4-dichlorobenzene Ham Diving suit Wallpaper Motor oil Bacon Hyperthermia Hard water White phosphorus incendiary Soy protein Swimming pool Hand washing Edible salt Sodium carbonate Detergent Hygiene Japanese tea ceremony Ironing Clothing Citric acid Sock Solvent Sugar Wart Weaving Procter & Gamble Western blot Car washing techniques Fecal incontinence Escherichia coli O157: